The paper deals with instance segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses a recurrent neural network (RNN) with an attention mechanism, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The attention mechanism is used to model a human-like counting process, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the application of instance segmentation in autonomous driving suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of robotics (cs.RO).
